<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>at a price • at the price</xh5><p> <i>at a price—</i>1. <i>bought or sold</i> at a high cost; very expensive: There’s fresh asparagus in the shops—<u>at a price</u>! 2. at the cost of much effort and sacrifice: Such is his grip on the market, though it is one obtained <u>at a price</u>.</p><p> <i>at the price—</i>1. at the cost indicated: Other wines difficult to beat <u>at the price</u> include three good dry whites from Hungary. 2. at the expense of smth.: The issue will be whether the government will introduce the harsh measures <u>at the price</u> of its own popularity.</p> </entry>
